# User Stories: AI-Powered Appraisal System

## Story Priority Definitions

| Priority | Meaning | Target Sprint |
|----------|---------|---------------|
| **P0** | Must-have for MVP; system cannot launch without it | Sprint 1-2 |
| **P1** | High value; should be included in first release | Sprint 3-4 |
| **P2** | Nice to have; can be deferred to post-MVP | Sprint 5+ |

---

## Role 1: Employee (Individual Contributor)

### US-EMP-01: View Performance Dashboard
**As an** Employee,
**I want** to see my real-time performance dashboard with my current score compared to team benchmark,
**so that** I understand where I stand before my formal appraisal.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
| Given | When | Then |
|-------|------|------|
| I am logged in as an employee | I navigate to My Dashboard | I see my current score (e.g., 90) and team benchmark (e.g., 85) |
| Performance data exists for current cycle | I view the trend chart | I see a line chart of my performance over last 6 months |
| My metrics dipped in a specific month | I load the dashboard | I see an alert banner explaining the dip and suggesting I add context |

**Priority:** P0
**Dependencies:** None (UI can mock data initially)

---

### US-EMP-02: Add Context to Metrics
**As an** Employee,
**I want** to add contextual notes explaining unusual metric patterns (like low commit activity during on-call weeks),
**so that** my manager understands the full picture and I am not penalized for expected fluctuations.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
| Given | When | Then |
|-------|------|------|
| I see a performance alert for April dip | I click "Add Context" | A form opens with the metric period pre-filled |
| I write an explanation and submit | I click "Submit Context" | My note is saved and visible to my manager |
| The system detects my context note | My manager views my appraisal | The note appears alongside the relevant metric |

**Priority:** P0
**Dependencies:** US-EMP-01 (Dashboard)

---

### US-EMP-03: Submit Self-Reported Achievements
**As an** Employee,
**I want** to add my own achievements like mentoring junior engineers or leading projects,
**so that** my manager sees contributions that may not appear in automated metrics.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
| Given | When | Then |
|-------|------|-------|
| I am on My Achievements section | I click "+ Add Achievement" | A form appears with fields for title, description, date, category |
| I fill in the details and submit | I click "Save" | My achievement is added to the list with "Pending Verification" status |
| My manager reviews my achievements | They view my profile | They see my self-reported achievements and can mark them verified |

**Priority:** P0
**Dependencies:** None

---

### US-EMP-04: Upload Supporting Artifacts
**As an** Employee,
**I want** to upload presentations, customer feedback, or design documents as evidence of my work,
**so that** I can provide concrete proof of my contributions.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
| Given | When | Then |
|-------|------|-------|
| I am on the Artifacts section | I drag and drop a file | The file uploads and shows a success confirmation |
| I have uploaded multiple files | I view my artifacts list | I see all uploaded files with names, dates, and types |
| I no longer need an artifact | I click delete | The artifact is removed from the system |

**Priority:** P1
**Dependencies:** US-EMP-03 (Achievements)

---

### US-EMP-05: View AI-Powered Improvement Suggestions
**As an** Employee,
**I want** to see AI-generated suggestions for skills I should develop,
**so that** I can proactively work on areas that will help my career growth.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
| Given | When | Then |
|-------|------|-------|
| The AI analyzes my performance gaps | I view my dashboard | I see suggestions like "Consider attending Leadership Essentials workshop" |
| I click on a suggestion | I interact with it | I see more details and a link to relevant learning resources |
| My performance improves in that area | AI re-evaluates | The suggestion may be marked as "In Progress" or removed |

**Priority:** P1
**Dependencies:** US-EMP-01 (Dashboard), AI Service

---

### US-EMP-06: Receive Early Warning of Performance Dips
**As an** Employee,
**I want** to receive alerts when my metrics show a downward trend,
**so that** I can address issues early rather than being surprised at review time.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
| Given | When | Then |
|-------|------|-------|
| My metrics drop for 2 consecutive sprints | The system detects the anomaly | I see a warning banner on my dashboard |
| I click on the warning | I expand it | I see specific metrics that declined and a prompt to add context |
| I add context explaining the dip | I submit it | The warning severity decreases or is dismissed |

**Priority:** P1
**Dependencies:** US-EMP-01 (Dashboard), Anomaly Detection Service

---

### US-EMP-07: See Which Data Points Contributed to My Review
**As an** Employee,
**I want** to see exactly which Jira tickets, commits, and feedback were used in my evaluation,
**so that** I trust the system is fair and transparent.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
| Given | When | Then |
|-------|------|-------|
| My manager has generated an AI draft | I view "What Data is Being Evaluated" | I see counts: Jira: 247, Git: 523, Feedback: 12 |
| I click on Jira data | I expand the section | I see a list of specific ticket IDs and titles |
| A data source is out of sync | I check the status | I see a "Last sync" timestamp and "Needs Update" indicator |

**Priority:** P0
**Dependencies:** US-MGR-02 (AI Draft Generation)

---

## Role 2: Engineering Manager

### US-MGR-01: View Team Dashboard
**As a** Engineering Manager,
**I want** to see a unified dashboard of all my direct reports with their appraisal completeness status,
**so that** I can quickly understand my team's progress and prioritize my time.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
| Given | When | Then |
|-------|------|-------|
| I am logged in as a manager with 6 team members | I navigate to Manager Dashboard | I see team size (6), AI drafts ready (4), and avg time per appraisal (25m) |
| I need to find a specific employee | I type in the search bar | The team list filters to show matching names |
| I want to see who is ready for review | I look at the status column | Each member shows "Ready to Review", "In Progress", or "Not Started" |

**Priority:** P0
**Dependencies:** None

---

### US-MGR-02: Generate AI Draft Appraisal
**As a** Engineering Manager,
**I want** the system to automatically generate a draft appraisal with cited data points for each employee,
**so that** I save 3-4 hours of manual prep work per employee.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
| Given | When | Then |
|-------|------|-------|
| I select an employee from my team | I click "Generate AI Draft" | The system returns a draft with rating (e.g., 4.2), strengths, and areas for improvement |
| The draft includes data citations | I expand a strength claim | I see source links: "PROJ-123: Implemented auth service", "Peer feedback from Marcus" |
| The AI detects potential bias | The draft is generated | I see bias flags like "Recency bias detected - recent work overweighted by 32%" |

**Priority:** P0
**Dependencies:** Data Integration (Jira, Git, Feedback APIs), AI Service

---

### US-MGR-03: Override AI Draft
**As a** Engineering Manager,
**I want** to edit, add comments, or override the AI-generated rating and narrative,
**so that** I can apply my human judgment where the AI might miss context.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
| Given | When | Then |
|-------|------|-------|
| I am viewing an AI draft | I click "Edit" on the rating | I can change 4.2 to 4.0 using a slider or number input |
| I want to add my own comments | I type in the manager comments field | My comments are saved alongside the AI narrative |
| I override a strength recommendation | I delete it and add my own | The system logs my override in the audit trail |

**Priority:** P0
**Dependencies:** US-MGR-02 (AI Draft Generation)

---

### US-MGR-04: Approve and Finalize Appraisal
**As a** Engineering Manager,
**I want** to lock and finalize an appraisal once I am satisfied,
**so that** the employee receives their official review and no further changes can be made.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
| Given | When | Then |
|-------|------|-------|
| I have completed editing the appraisal | I click "Approve & Finalize" | A confirmation modal asks "Are you sure? This will lock the appraisal." |
| I confirm the action | I click "Yes, Finalize" | The status changes from "Draft" to "Approved" |
| I try to edit an approved appraisal | I click on it | Edit buttons are disabled; I see "This appraisal has been finalized" |

**Priority:** P0
**Dependencies:** US-MGR-03 (Override AI Draft)

---

### US-MGR-05: Compare Team Ratings for Calibration
**As a** Engineering Manager,
**I want** to see how my team's ratings compare to organizational averages,
**so that** I can identify if I am being too lenient or too harsh.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
| Given | When | Then |
|-------|------|-------|
| I have finalized at least 3 appraisals | I view the Calibration tab | I see my team's average rating (4.6) vs org average (4.0) |
| My rating is significantly higher than org average | I view the comparison | I see a flag: "Your ratings are 0.6 points above average - consider review" |
| I click on the suggestion | I accept the AI recommendation | I can adjust ratings with one click to bring them in line |

**Priority:** P1
**Dependencies:** US-MGR-04 (Finalize Appraisal), HR Calibration Service

---

### US-MGR-06: View Audit Trail of My Edits
**As a** Engineering Manager,
**I want** to see a log of all AI recommendations I accepted or overrode,
**so that** I can justify my decisions during HR calibration reviews.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
| Given | When | Then |
|-------|------|-------|
| I have overridden 3 AI suggestions | I click "Audit Trail" for an employee | I see entries: "Override: Changed rating from 4.2 to 4.0", "Override: Removed improvement suggestion" |
| HR is reviewing my team | They access the audit log | They see timestamps, original AI values, and my overrides |
| A compliance audit occurs | The auditor requests logs | I can export the audit trail as CSV |

**Priority:** P1
**Dependencies:** US-MGR-03 (Override AI Draft)

---

## Role 3: HR Business Partner

### US-HR-01: View Calibration Dashboard
**As an** HR Business Partner,
**I want** to see the overall appraisal cycle progress and key metrics,
**so that** I can ensure the cycle completes within the 2-week goal.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
| Given | When | Then |
|-------|------|-------|
| The appraisal cycle is active | I navigate to HR Calibration Dashboard | I see completion rate (38/45, 84%), days in cycle (12/14), and goal status |
| A manager is falling behind | I view the dashboard | I see a warning for that manager to prioritize completion |
| Calibration meetings are scheduled | I view the dashboard | I see meetings held (2) and scheduled (2) |

**Priority:** P0
**Dependencies:** US-MGR-04 (Finalize Appraisal)

---

### US-HR-02: View AI-Flagged Calibration Issues
**As an** HR Business Partner,
**I want** to see automatically flagged issues like rating outliers, low consistency, or bias patterns,
**so that** I can intervene before unfair appraisals are finalized.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
| Given | When | Then |
|-------|------|-------|
| A manager's team has rating outliers | I view Calibration Issues | I see an issue: "John Smith: 2 outlier ratings detected" with MEDIUM severity |
| A manager shows gender bias pattern | I expand that issue | I see detail: "Female employees rated 0.3 points lower than males - 5 affected" |
| I want to resolve an issue | I click "Schedule Calibration Session" | A modal opens to invite the manager and set a meeting time |

**Priority:** P0
**Dependencies:** AI Bias Detection Service, US-MGR-04 (Finalize Appraisal)

---

### US-HR-03: View Manager Consistency Analysis
**As an** HR Business Partner,
**I want** to see a table comparing all managers by team size, average rating, standard deviation, and outliers,
**so that** I can identify which managers need calibration support.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
| Given | When | Then |
|-------|------|-------|
| I have data from multiple managers | I view Manager Consistency table | I see rows for Alex Rivera (8 team, 4.2 rating, 0.45 std dev, 0 outliers, 92% consistency) |
| A manager has low consistency score | I scan the Status column | I see "Review Needed" for Maria Garcia and John Smith |
| I click on a manager's row | I expand it | I see detailed team rating distribution and outlier details |

**Priority:** P0
**Dependencies:** US-MGR-04 (Finalize Appraisal)

---

### US-HR-04: View Organization Rating Distribution
**As an** HR Business Partner,
**I want** to see a chart of rating distribution across the entire organization,
**so that** I can ensure there is no grade inflation or forced curve distortion.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
| Given | When | Then |
|-------|------|-------|
| Appraisals are completed across org | I view Rating Distribution chart | I see a bar chart with counts for ratings 1.0 through 5.0 |
| The distribution shows unexpected spikes | I hover over the 4.5 bar | I see a tooltip: "15 employees (33%) - mostly from Engineering" |
| I want to investigate further | I click on the bar | I see a filtered list of employees with that rating |

**Priority:** P1
**Dependencies:** US-MGR-04 (Finalize Appraisal)

---

### US-HR-05: Access Compliance Audit Logs
**As an** HR Business Partner,
**I want** to view all AI recommendations and manager overrides with timestamps and user details,
**so that** I can demonstrate GDPR/SOC2 compliance during audits.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
| Given | When | Then |
|-------|------|-------|
| I need to respond to a compliance audit | I navigate to Audit Logs | I see a complete list of 137 AI recommendations and 23 manager overrides |
| I want to filter by manager | I select "John Smith" from filter | I see only actions performed by John Smith |
| I need to export for auditors | I click "Export CSV" | A CSV file downloads with all audit log entries |

**Priority:** P0
**Dependencies:** US-MGR-03 (Override AI Draft), Audit Logging Service

---

### US-HR-06: Export Audit Trail for Dispute Resolution
**As an** HR Business Partner,
**I want** to export a detailed audit trail for a specific employee appraisal,
**so that** I can provide evidence during a performance review dispute.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
| Given | When | Then |
|-------|------|-------|
| An employee disputes their rating | I search for the employee by name | I see their appraisal with all data sources used |
| I need to show what the AI recommended | I expand "AI Draft History" | I see original AI rating (4.2) and narrative |
| I need to show manager changes | I expand "Manager Overrides" | I see manager changed rating to 4.0 and added comments |

**Priority:** P1
**Dependencies:** US-HR-05 (Audit Logs)

---

## Role 4: Senior Leader / Director

### US-LDR-01: View Org-Level Talent Summary
**As a** Senior Leader,
**I want** to see high-level KPIs including flight risk percentage, high-performers count, and promotion readiness,
**so that** I can make informed talent investment decisions.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
| Given | When | Then |
|-------|------|-------|
| I am logged in as a Director | I navigate to Org Summary | I see high-performers (12), flight risk (8%), promotion-ready (6) |
| I want to see which teams have highest flight risk | I expand the section | I see a breakdown by team/department |
| I click on a high-performer | I view their profile | I see their trajectory, recent achievements, and manager's recommendation |

**Priority:** P1
**Dependencies:** US-MGR-04 (Finalize Appraisal)

---

### US-LDR-02: View Manager Effectiveness Ranking
**As a** Senior Leader,
**I want** to see a ranking of managers by team performance and calibration fairness,
**so that** I can identify which managers need coaching or are ready for promotion.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
| Given | When | Then |
|-------|------|-------|
| Calibration data is available | I view Manager Effectiveness | I see managers ranked by team performance vs target and calibration score |
| A manager has high team performance but low calibration | I expand their row | I see details: "Team avg 4.6 vs org 4.0 - Possible leniency bias" |
| I want to schedule coaching | I click "Request HR Review" | An alert is sent to HR to schedule a calibration session |

**Priority:** P2
**Dependencies:** US-HR-02 (Calibration Issues)

---

### US-LDR-03: Identify Promotion Candidates
**As a** Senior Leader,
**I want** to see employees with trajectory scores above promotion threshold,
**so that** I can proactively plan promotions and succession.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
| Given | When | Then |
|-------|------|-------|
| The system has analyzed performance trends | I view Promotion Candidates | I see a list of employees with trajectory scores > 90th percentile |
| I want to see supporting evidence | I click on an employee | I see their performance trend chart, achievements, and manager recommendation |
| I need to compare two candidates | I select both employees | I see a side-by-side comparison of metrics and trajectories |

**Priority:** P2
**Dependencies:** US-MGR-04 (Finalize Appraisal), AI Trajectory Service

---

## Role 5: System / Admin

### US-ADM-01: Sync Data from Jira
**As a** System Administrator,
**I want** to manually trigger Jira ticket sync or configure automatic sync schedules,
**so that** employee metrics stay up to date without manual data entry.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
| Given | When | Then |
|-------|------|-------|
| Jira integration is configured | I click "Sync Jira" | The system pulls ticket completion, story points, and bug data |
| The sync encounters an API rate limit | The process runs | The sync pauses and resumes, logging the rate limit event |
| A sync completes successfully | I check integration status | I see "Last sync: 2026-05-12, Up to date" for Jira |

**Priority:** P0
**Dependencies:** Jira API Access

---

### US-ADM-02: Configure Scoring Weights
**As a** System Administrator,
**I want** to adjust the weight percentages for Jira, Git, feedback, and self-assessments,
**so that** the organization can emphasize different priorities (e.g., more weight on peer feedback).

**Acceptance Criteria:**
| Given | When | Then |
|-------|------|-------|
| I have admin privileges | I navigate to Scoring Configuration | I see sliders for Jira (40%), Git (20%), Feedback (30%), Self (10%) |
| I adjust Jira to 50% and Git to 10% | I click Save | The new weights are applied to all future AI draft generations |
| An HR user tries to change weights | They access the page | They see a "Permission Denied" message |

**Priority:** P1
**Dependencies:** US-MGR-02 (AI Draft Generation)

---

### US-ADM-03: Start and Close Appraisal Cycles
**As a** System Administrator,
**I want** to create a new appraisal cycle with start/end dates and deadlines,
**so that** the system knows which period to evaluate.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
| Given | When | Then |
|-------|------|-------|
| The previous cycle is closed | I click "Start New Cycle" | I enter cycle name "H2 2026", start date, end date, and deadlines |
| I submit the form | I click Create | The cycle becomes active and appears on all user dashboards |
| The cycle end date passes | I click "Close Cycle" | All pending appraisals are locked and data is archived |

**Priority:** P0
**Dependencies:** None

---

### US-ADM-04: Monitor Integration Health
**As a** System Administrator,
**I want** to see the status of all external integrations (Jira, Git, LMS) with last sync timestamps and error counts,
**so that** I can quickly identify and fix failed syncs before they affect appraisal data.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
| Given | When | Then |
|-------|------|-------|
| An integration fails to sync | I view Integration Status | I see a red indicator for that integration with error details |
| A sync has been running for hours | I check the status | I see "Running" with a cancel button to stop it |
| A webhook is misconfigured | I view webhook logs | I see failed delivery attempts with HTTP error codes |

**Priority:** P1
**Dependencies:** US-ADM-01 (Sync Data)

